race.comment: Tough finish. BUDJIK BOY (3) is going well and should get a decent run here. He tried hard in a stronger race at Hamilton last time, tracking the speed and kicking on well for third. He now gets to 1800m which only suits better and with a repeat of last time he should go close. CHAIRMAN (2) is knocking on the door with three minor placings in a row. He just missed in the Coleraine Cup last time with 55kg and this is a fair bit easier. Should take beating. ONGATITI (10) is relatively lightly raced and presents third up having been about the mark in two runs back. Ready to peak now from the gun gate. MR GEORGE (7) is flying having won his past two in much easier company. Have to respect.
